An Act regulating drones.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 90 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition, is hereby
2 amended by inserting, after section 39G, the following:-
3 Section 39H. For the purposes of this section, the following words shall have the
4 following meanings, unless the context clearly requires otherwise:
5 “Unmanned Aerial Vehicle”, “UAV”, or “drone” shall mean a powered aerial vehicle
6 that: (i) does not carry a human operator and is operated without the possibility of direct human
7 intervention from within or on the aircraft; (ii) uses aerodynamic forces to provide vehicle lift;
8 (iii) can fly autonomously or be piloted remotely; (iv) can be expendable or recoverable; and (v.)
9 weighs less than 55lbs.
10 “Chinese state-owned company” shall mean any corporation, business, association,
11 partnership, venture, limited liability company, or other entity or business association owned
12 fully or in part by, or affiliated with, the government of China.
